A man was rescued at Lions Head in Cape Town on Thursday after falling during his hike.The 38-year-old man was hiking when he fell down a steep slope for about twenty metres.Chris Botha for Netcare911 said &#8220;A joint rescue effort between Netcare911 paramedics, Wilderness search and rescue, Metro search and rescue and Skymed Helicopter ensured the safe rescue of the man&#8221;.&#8220;The rescue team found the patient and after he was stabilised they airlifted him to a meeting point with the Netcare 911 ambulance&#8221;, said Botha.The man sustained moderate injuries and was transported by ambulance, under the constant care of an advanced Life Support paramedic to a specialised hospital for further treatment.-TNA Reporter